  "title": "Site Manager",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Organise Kickoff meeting and presentation on planned schedule and work scope</li>\n  <li>Maintain good working relationship with contractors and other subcontractors</li>\n  <li>Monitor the performance of subcontractors &amp; quality of finished products</li>\n  <li>Plan schedule, expedite progress and to resolve late schedule/progress</li>\n  <li>Works with Operations team on deployment of manpower and necessary arrangement</li>\n  <li>Ad-hoc duties such as general administration duties, follow up billing dispute with suppliers</li>\n  <li>Upkeep the Health and Safety standards, objectives &amp; targets on all job sites</li>\n  <li>Works closely together with the QC Manager to ensure that standards are met and compatible with the various job requirements</li>\n  <li>Prepare monthly report to superior</li>\n  <li>Liaise &amp; negotiate with suppliers and subcontractors on better pricing of products</li>\n  <li>To understand and modify design structurally and architecturally on company’s benefits.</li>\n  <li>Leading and mentoring a team by setting guidelines and procedure.</li>\n  <li>Plan and define program, goal device method to accomplish them develop in depth knowledge of client objectives contract term and corporate policies.</li>\n  <li>To oversee project team, coordinates with client, sub- contractor, and consultants for delivery of project in accordance with contract completion stipulated phases.</li>\n  <li>To insure Safety Health, Environment practice are carried out at all times.</li>\n  <li>Coordinates and supervise the construction process and activities on site from the conceptual development stage through final construction.</li>\n  <li>Monitor project time cost, quality, scope, resource and risk management</li>\n  <li>To submit progress claim, monthly report, oversee scheduling and other managerial aspect of project.</li>\n</ul>",
